cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about video prediction, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses LSTMs and convolutional auto-encoder networks, which are common in deep learning and machine learning research, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper uses adversarial loss, which is a technique commonly used in generative models, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) may also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on a dataset, indicating that cs.MM (Multimedia) may also be a relevant category.
